The paper's focus on improving execution flexibility suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, which deals with robot control and motion planning. The paper's use of heuristics and empirical evaluation suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category, which deals with algorithms that can learn from data. Finally, the paper's focus on handling metric and temporal constraints suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category, which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems.
